miscConds.notes:
During the pendency of this deferral, the Defendant agrees to: Commit no acts which rise to the level of probable cause in violation of the criminal laws of the State of Wisconsin, or of any state, or of the United States of America. Comply with all conditions of bail or bond in this case. Pay a fine of $20. The victim in this case is not requesting restitution.
The parties agree, and the Defendant understands, that the condition of any bail or bond in effect on the plea date shall continue for the entire length of this agreement, and that any violation of the Defendant's bond may result in bail jumping charges pursuant to Wis Statute 946.49. The Defendant further understand that a charged violation of the bail or bond for which probable cause is found shall be a basis for the State to vacate this agreement. The parties also stipulate to a reduction to signature bond for the one remaining misdemeanor count is appropriate. Orders of no contact remain in effect. 
Defendant will keep Douglas County Clerk of Courts informed of his address and telephone number at all times, and stipulates that the sending of notice by regular mail to the address on file with the Clerk of Courts constitutes sufficient notice of any court hearings scheduled in this matter.  The non-appearance of the defendant may result in the issuance of an arrest warrant. 
If, at any time during the deferral period, the Defendant has not complied with the conditions of this agreement, the State may at its discretion and upon notice the defendant, revoke this agreement and move the Court to enter the judgment of conviction and the parties shall proceed to sentencing. At sentencing, if this agreement is revoked, the State will ask the court to enter judgment and to fine the defendant $200 in addition to the costs as ordered in the conviction for Count 3 of this same agreement.

Except as otherwise provided in this agreement, the State must prove non-compliance with this agreement by the preponderance of evidence at a hearing subject to Wis. Stat. 911.01(4)(c).
At the end of the deferral period or upon completion of all terms of this agreement, whichever is later, the Defendant has complies with the conditions of this agreement and provided proof of compliance when required, the State will move to dismiss Count 2 with prejudice.

records.addlTxt: No contact with Victim 1 or 2 and their addresses. No contact with Centerfolds.

1:01 PM Defendant Dewayne Lamonte Jackson in court, in custody.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Dewayne Lamonte Jackson.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. State recites agreement that defendant to plead to Count 2 and Count 3. Counts 1 and 4 are to be dismissed. For Count 2, a deferred judgment of conviction. For Count 3, serve 140 days jail with credit for 105 days and pay a $20 fine plus costs.  State has complied with Victim's Rights. For Count 2 and 3, Defendant pleads guilty to charge.  Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.  The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea.  The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is deferred pursuant to the terms of the agreement. For Count 3, serve 140 days jail with credit for 105 days and pay a $20 fine plus costs. Attorney Anderson stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.

Court orders for Count 3, serve 140 days jail with credit for 105 days and pay a $20 fine plus costs. Count 1 and 4 are dismissed. Court amends defendant's cash bond to a $2,000 signature bond with conditions of no contact with Victim 1 or 2 and their addresses. No contact with Centerfolds.

1:10 PM Defendant Dewayne Lamonte Jackson appeared by video.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Dewayne Lamonte Jackson.  Attorney Chad La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Anderson notes defendant in Indiana. States he could post $1,000 cash bail. Defendant unsure if he can post that amount. State is opposed to bail modification, notes lack of ties and severe charges pending. Defendant missed Court in Hennepin Co in Feb 2022 and extradition was waived. Court reviews on failure to appear and pending warrant. State notes an arrest in Alabama on record. Court notes lack of ties and questions local address. Attorney Anderson does not have an local address. Court concerned of no local address to stay. Court denies bail modification.

11:41 AM Defendant Dewayne Lamonte Jackson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court via video for Dewayne Lamonte Jackson.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Anderson received information, waives reading and pleads not guilty. Attorney Anderson requests a speedy trial. Court accepts not guilty pleas. Court sets PTC and Jury Trial dates. Attorney Anderson asks for bail modification hearing. Court sets bail/bond hearing.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
Jury trial scheduled for July 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Bail/bond hearing scheduled for May 2, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

03:07 PM Defendant Dewayne Lamonte Jackson in court with attorney Ellen Craker.  Defendant Dewayne Lamonte Jackson in custody. Angela Wilson  appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dewayne Lamonte Jackson appeared by video means with Attorney.  Address verified as 6856 Stinson Court, Mobile, AL 36608.  Craker acknowledges complaint, waives reading, ask for preliminary hearing, not guilty to misdemeanor counts. Court accepts not guilty pleas. State asks for $10,000 cash, no contact with victim 1 or 2 or either of their residences. no contact with centerfolds in Superior or University of Minnesota Campus in Minneapolis. Cites defendant is an out of state resident. Cites priors in MN and Alabama. Victim is a student at University. 
Attorney Craker believes no contact at University is overly broad. no contact with victims is sufficient. Amount of cash not necessary, has employment prospects in Minnesota. No crimnial history in WI or MN. No cash to post.
Court orders $2,000 cash, with conditions of no contact with Victim 1 or 2, or their addresses. Does not feel no contact with University necessary. No contact with Centerfolds. Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 30, 2022 at 09:15 am.
